News of late activities by School of the commoning UK:

"Last Friday we had another very successful Meeting with Remarkable Commoners. Thanks to our crowdfunding campaign <http://www.indiegogo.com/CommonsCampaign/> reaching its first goal, we managed to bring James Quilligan to London and he gave a seminar on Managing the Local and Global Commons to 30 people in the audience, which opened doors to collaborative alliances with other groups in London. We are going to blog about it and let you know if you want to want to read the story.

We are also working on creating a Social Charter <http://globalcommonstrust.org/?page_id=20/> for the School of Commoning that is in the process of merging with the Commons Learning Alliance and the online Commons Campus under the SoC brand. The merger turns our London based team into an autonomous circle of the international School of Commoning. I told my colleagues about your plans and everybody was very enthused about supporting it in any way we can. May it contribute to the emergence of a global field of commons education and the awakening of the commons movement to its full potential!"

